ion\/\" class=\"elementor-item\" tabindex=\"-1\">International energy efficiency certification<\/a><\/li>\n<li class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-object-page menu-item-12668\"><a href=\"https:\/\/pangminybm.com\/services\/class-and-statutory\/international-antifouling-systems-certification\/\" class=\"elementor-item\" tabindex=\"-1\">International antifouling systems certificate (IAFS)<\/a><\/li>\n<li class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-object-page menu-item-12644\"><a href=\"https:\/\/pangminybm.com\/services\/class-and-statutory\/document-of-compliance-with-the-special-requirements-for-ships-carrying-dangerous-goods\/\" class=\"elementor-item\" tabindex=\"-1\">Document of compliance for the carriage of solid bulk cargoes<\/a><\/li>\n<li class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-object-page menu-item-12657\"><a href=\"https:\/\/pangminybm.com\/services\/class-and-statutory\/ballast-water-management-certification\/\" class=\"elementor-item\" tabindex=\"-1\">International ballast water management\u00a0certificate<\/a><\/li>\n<li class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-object-page menu-item-12664\"><a href=\"https:\/\/pangminybm.com\/services\/class-and-statutory\/dangerous-goods-certification\/\" class=\"elementor-item\" tabindex=\"-1\">Document of Compliance with the Special Requirements for Ships Carrying Dangerous Goods<\/a><\/li>\n<li class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-object-page menu-item-12667\"><a href=\"https:\/\/pangminybm.com\/international-certificate-on-inventory-of-hazardous-material\/\" class=\"elementor-item\" tabindex=\"-1\">Hong Kong international convention for the safe and environmentally sound recycling of ships, 2009<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\t\t\t<\/nav>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-62fc2b5e\" data-id=\"62fc2b5e\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-95b0b4b elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"95b0b4b\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">International Convention on Load Lines:<\/h3>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-72940aa elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"72940aa\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<ul><li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Adopted: 5th of April 1966<\/span><\/li><li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Entry into force: 21st July 1968<\/span><\/li><li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Main objectives:<\/span><ul><li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">to ensure weather-tight and watertight integrity of ships<\/span><\/li><li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">To specify maximum safe draft the ship can sail on by assigning minimum freeboards<\/span><\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-01797a0 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"01797a0\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">International load line certificate:<\/h3>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-73aaa75 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"73aaa75\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Application:<\/h3>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-9cfab3f elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"9cfab3f\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">International Load Line certificate is not required for the following ships:<\/span><\/p><ul><li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">New ships of load line length less than 24 m<\/span><\/li><li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Existing ships of less than 150 gross tonnage<\/span><\/li><li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Pleasure yachts not used for commercial purpose<\/span><\/li><li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Fishing vessels.<\/span><\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-01882be elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"01882be\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Survey loop:<\/h3>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-0440d38 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"0440d38\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">A ship under certification for International load line certificate is subject to the following surveys<\/span><\/p><ul><li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Initial survey: when the vessel is firstly certified<\/span><\/li><li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">First annual survey: at the first anniversary date of the initial survey with a window of 3 months before or 3 months after<\/span><\/li><li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Second annual survey:at the second anniversary date of the initial survey with a window of 3 months before or 3 months after<\/span><\/li><li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Intermediate survey: normally it is due at the middle of the five years loop with a window of 6 months before or after, but practically is carried out at the third anniversary date\u00a0<\/span><\/li><li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Fourth annual survey::at the fourth anniversary date of the initial survey with a window of 3 months before or 3 months after<\/span><\/li><li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Renewal survey: At the firth anniversary date of the initial survey with a window of 3 months before it, but can not be shifted after the full term certificate is expired<\/span><\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-82e727b elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"82e727b\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Procedure for certification:<\/h3>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-b0a6065 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"b0a6065\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<ul><li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Conducting of scheduled survey<\/span><\/li><li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Rectification of deficiency or recommendations if applicable<\/span><\/li><li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Issuance of Interim International load line certificate valid for 5 months (according to the International convention on load lines can be issued up to 6 months and majority of recognized organization issue the interim for only 5 months)<\/span><\/li><li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">In most cases the interim International load line certificate is issued by the attending surveyor<\/span><\/li><li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Survey reports and supporting documents to be filed and sent to recognized organization head office for review<\/span><\/li><li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Upon satisfactory results of the review, recognized organization HO office issues full term International Load line certification valid for 5 years from the date of the survey<\/span><\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elemen